\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\q=q_{0}+q_{x}i+q_{y}j+q_{z}k.
\]

\end_inset

Here you can see two additional imaginary numbers, 
\begin_inset Formula $j$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $k$
\end_inset

.
 These new imaginary numbers follow the following rules
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
i^{2}=j^{2}=k^{2}=ijk=-1,
\]

\end_inset

